LUMPY SKIN DISEASE, BOVINE - CYPRUS (02): (NORTHERN CYPRUS), REQUEST FOR INFORMATION
************************************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

[1]
Date: Tue 9 Dec 2014
Source: Kibris [in Turkish, machine trans. summarized, edited]
http://www.kibrisgazetesi.com/?p=589201


Since the 1st detection of lumpy skin disease [LSD] in the village Sipahi last week, the disease has spread. Yesterday [8 Dec 2014], a bull and 6 cows were culled. This brings the total of affected cows to 11 [pictures of culling activities included].

[Byline: Ayse Bulut]

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

******
[2]
Date: Mon 8 Dec 2014
Source: Kibris [in Turkish, machine trans. summarized, edited]
http://www.kibrisgazetesi.com/?p=589020


The LSD outbreak in Northern Cyprus was discussed during meetings of the Greek-Turkish technical health committee. The [Cypriotic] Greek Minister of Agriculture, Kuylis said today [8 Dec 2014] that the information will be forwarded to Brussels [EU]. [A picture of LSD-affected cattle is included].

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[According to information in other local media sources, the authorities in the ["Greek"] Republic of Cyprus have undertaken measures to prevent the introduction of the disease from Northern Cyprus. Information on the said measures is requested. In case vaccination is considered, details on the vaccine strain to be applied will be appreciated. - Mod.AS

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=3022793,82.]
